•Whale Watching• 

Yesterdays conditions out on the water were absolutely perfect and a bit unique! While filming these bow riding dolphins you could see how much surface tension the ocean had. Normally when the dolphins get close to the surface they poke through pretty easily but watch the reflection of the clouds bend as the center dolphin gets close to the top. One minute it’s flat with a perfect reflection and the next you see a crazy amount of warp which I thought was super cool! This was filmed in 1080 120fps on the iPhone 14 Pro Max. Taken aboard @pacificoffshore

•Mars Occultation•

Last night Mars disappeared behind the moon for about an hour and then popped back out. The planets located at the top right corner where you can see the tiny little orange dot. This picture is a stack of around 40 images that I took it around 7:30pm. Did any of you get to see it?

•Jupiter• 

Last month I had the opportunity to hang out at the @mtwilsonobservatory which was amazing! Huge shoutout to @mostly_star_stuff for making the night happen and @thekevingreene for inviting me. I was also able to attach my camera on the telescope for a bit and photograph Jupiter. 7,000 frames extracted from video were used to create this image. I’m really happy with the results and can’t wait to go back one day.

•Yosemite•

Two years ago I was in Yosemite capturing this video of the amazing phenomenon known as Firefall. This happens during the month of February when the sun hits Horsetail Fall. The waterfall is backlit by the sun setting which creates the color. If you’ve never seen this in person I highly recommend going!

•LA Chinatown• 

I recently picked up the @fujifilmx_us X100V and I’m absolutely loving it. I wanted a smaller camera to bridge the gap between my iPhone and the Sonys I shoot on. Something to take everywhere that can easily fit in my pocket but still produce great images. All of these pictures are straight out of the camera with no editing done at all. Being able to program recipes into it to get a certain look is my favorite part. I’m really looking forward to testing it out more. Shot alongside @timosumida & @beef0fthesea

These whales were only about 30 feet away from the shore and the combination of water clarity with it being so shallow made this day special. I can’t wait to show more! Filmed on my @djiglobal Mavic 3 and shot alongside my good friend @jayxlamar

•Bioluminescence•

We’ve all seen sand crabs before on the beach but have you ever seen them light up from bioluminescence? Last night I experienced this for the first time at Emma Wood State Beach and it was amazing! You can see the individual crabs glow after the water rushes back. It’s been a while since I’ve shared my voice in these videos so here ya go. 😂 This was extremely challenging to film because of how dark it was so my ISO was at 256,000. Not the cleanest footage I’ve taken but it’s too cool not to share.

The absolute best days of my life are spent out on the ocean and yesterday was a perfect example of that. We had the pleasure of seeing 10 ETP Killer Whales off the South Bay coast!
